			<a href="mailto:hello@dillonbrown.me" style="text-decoration-color: #FFBD21;">Contact</a>
			<a href="/pdf/resume.pdf" style="text-decoration-color: #75D70A;">Résumé</a>
		</nav>
	</header>
	
	<!-- APP MOCKUPS
	–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––– -->
	<style>
		body {
			background: white;
			color: black;
		}
		h6 {
			color: #FFC900;
		}
		.blue-gradient {
			background-image: linear-gradient(134deg, #4899F7 0%, #2457F5 100%);
		}
		.blue a {
			text-decoration-color: #387BF6;
		}
		.blue a:hover {
			color: #387BF6;
		}
		a {
			text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
		}
	</style>
	
	<main>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns">
				<h1 style="color: #387BF6;">Mac Podcast App</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row blue">
			<div class="eight columns">
				<p>Podcasts on macOS don't get the love they deserve. I would like to change that with an app I call Power Casts.</p>
				<p>Somewhere in the creation of this mockup I realized I borrowed a lot from the exemplary <a href="https://ranchero.com/netnewswire/">NetNewsWire</a>. So I forked <a href="https://github.com/brentsimmons/NetNewsWire"> their repo on GitHub</a> and hope to use it to build my dream macOS podcast app. Someday...</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
	
	<div class="row ">
		<div class="twelve columns">
			<a href="https://www.sketch.com/s/16415261-13d8-46dd-83cf-5090452bcaf0/a/wJrd7w/play">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/podcast-app.png" alt="">
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>

	<main>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns">
				<h1 style="color:#FFBD21;">Mobile Audio Apps</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="eight columns">
				<p>There are more music apps than ever. However, few of them are made for people like me. Instead of renting music from Spotify, I buy my own copy from sites like Bandcamp. Additionally, I have other kinds of audio files, like audiobooks, stand-up comedy albums, and epic longform podcasts no longer in a feed.</p>
				<p>I want to make a suite of apps laser-focused on one medium each. I envision these audio apps sharing a codebase for much of their functionality and similar interfaces, each tailored to their content.</p>
			</div>
		</div>	
	</main>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="twelve columns">
			<!-- <a href="https://www.sketch.com/s/e49ab05e-0fa9-48e8-b87e-f40c4396d529"> -->
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-hero.png" alt="">
			<!-- </a> -->
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<!--
		PODCASTS
	-->
	<section>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns center">
				<h3 style="color:#FFBD21;">Podcasts</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
		
	<div class="row" style="background: #F0F0F0; padding: 5rem 0; margin-bottom: 5rem;">
		<section>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="four offset-by-two columns">
					<h5>Pocket Casts</h5>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns right-align">
					<h5>Mine</h5>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
				<div class="two columns right-align">
					<p>This is how a leading podcast app looks on a 4-inch iPhone screen.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/pocket-casts-1.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-1.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="two columns">
					<p>My design introduces a finger-friendly waveform scrubber. The scrubber can be moved from any point across the width of the phone.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
				<div class="two columns right-align">
					<p>This is how Pocket Casts presents a custom episode. </p>
					<p>The files name is used instead of its metadata and "Custom Episode" takes the place of useful information.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/pocket-casts-2.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-2.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="two columns">
					<p>A talented artist put a lot of detail in the artwork, and with my design you can see it.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
				<div class="two columns right-align">
					<p>Swipe to the left to see show notes. An additional swipe does not move to the queue, as the icon placement would suggest.</p>
					<p>On this screen you can not control playback, but you are informed of the full episode length &mdash; in minutes.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/pocket-casts-3.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-3.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="two columns">
					<p>From the main player screen, swipe up or tap the bottom buttons for additional functionality.</p>
					<p>The scrubber and playback buttons stay on screen. Swipe left or right to move to the queue or settings.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	<!--
		MUSIC
	-->
	<section>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns center">
				<h3 style="color:#FFBD21;">Music</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
		
	<div class="row" style="background: #F0F0F0; padding: 5rem 0; margin-bottom: 5rem;">
		<section>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="four offset-by-two columns">
					<h5>Apple Music</h5>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns right-align">
					<h5>Mine</h5>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
				<div class="two columns right-align">
					<p>Apple Music <i>can</i> play your MP3s, but when you first launch the app there is no mention of this feature.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/apple-music-1.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-4.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="two columns">
					<p><strong>Tap</strong> on the artwork to play or pause.</p>
					<p><strong>Swipe</strong> left or right to change tracks. </p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
				<div class="two columns right-align">
					<p>...</p>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="https://picsum.photos/640/1136" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-6.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="two columns">
					<p>Your queue, settings, equalizer, and lyrics are one tap away.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	<!--
		STAND-UP COMEDY
	-->
	<section>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns center">
				<h3 style="color:#FFBD21;">Stand-Up Comedy</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
		
	<div class="row" style="background: #F0F0F0; padding: 5rem 0; margin-bottom: 5rem;">
		<section>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="four offset-by-two columns">
					<h5>...</h5>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns right-align">
					<h5>Mine</h5>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">
				<div class="two columns right-align">
					<p>...</p>
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="https://picsum.photos/640/1136" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="four columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/music-app-5.png" alt="">
				</div>
				<div class="two columns">
					<p>Instead of your comedy albums getting lost in your music library, they live in their own app.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	

	<!--
		COOKBOOK APP
	-->
	<section>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns">
				<h1 style="color:#75D70A;">Cookbook App</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="eight columns">
				<p>I lose my place in cookbook apps and websites all the time. My idea adds colors, columns, and cleverness. Just look at those useful features &mdash; two columns so you are less likely to lose your place, color-coded ingredients, and in-line timers.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
		
	<div class="row">
		<div class="twelve columns">
			<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/app-concepts/recipe-app.png" alt="">
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>